<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 19 at 6:25PM MST until December 20 at 5:00AM MST by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST MONDAY...
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations between 3 and 6
inches...resulting in total snow accumulations of 6 to 9 inches.
* WHERE...Central and Southern Lewis and Clark County...including
the Helena valley.
* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Monday.
* IMPACTS...Roads will be slippery. Call 511 for current road
conditions.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow, heavy at times, will affect the Helena
valley through tonight. Visibility will be reduced to less than
one half mile at times.</description>
